# {{lb|en|medicine|American spelling}} Presence of [[glucose]] in the [[blood]] (which is always true), and {{lb|en|usually, more specifically}} average concentration thereof over time, and its regulation; in this sense, glycemia is [[hypernym]]ic to [[euglycemia]], [[hyperglycemia]], and [[hypoglycemia]], and a mention of glycemia is a reference to blood sugar regulation and degree or quality thereof.
